==English==

===Adjective===


#In Catholicism, a title indicating the [[beatification]] of a person, thus allowing public [[veneration]] of those who have lived in [[sanctity]] or died as [[martyr]]s.
#having [[divine]] aid, or protection, or other [[blessing]].


===Verb===


#To honor as holy; glorify: Bless the Lord. 
#To invoke divine favor upon.
#A past tense and a past participle of bless.

